WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:05.665
NARRATOR: Chester's Mill is a place
like any other. At least it used to be.

00:05.964 --> 00:07.795
[RUMBUNG]

00:08.008 --> 00:10.750
Until we were cut off from the rest of
the world by a mysterious dome.

00:11.094 --> 00:12.300
[THUMP]

00:12.513 --> 00:13.923
[oow MOOING]

00:14.681 --> 00:18.720
Invisible, indestructible
and completely inescapable.

00:18.936 --> 00:20.722
We're trapped.

00:20.938 --> 00:23.350
NARRATOR: We don't know where
it came from or why it's here,

00:23.565 --> 00:25.726
but now that we ’re all trapped
under the dome together,

00:25.943 --> 00:27.479
none of our secrets are safe.

00:27.903 --> 00:29.609
JULIA: Who the hell are you?
BARBIE: Barbie.

00:29.821 --> 00:31.686
People just call me Barbie.
It's a nickname.

00:31.907 --> 00:34.148
My husband isn't here,
but he'll turn up, you'll see.

00:34.785 --> 00:36.741
What do we do when people ask
about the propane?

00:36.954 --> 00:38.740
- That's your business.
- Heh, heh, heh.

00:40.123 --> 00:41.784
Duke, is it your pacemaker?

00:42.000 --> 00:43.501
- Ah!
- Stop!

00:43.710 --> 00:45.120
No one can hear us
all the way down here.

00:45.337 --> 00:46.702
ANGIE:
Let me out of here! Ah!

00:46.922 --> 00:48.378
- Junior.
- Dad.

00:48.590 --> 00:51.252
JULIA: You can stay with me.
Come on, I'll give you the nickel tour.

00:53.804 --> 00:54.839
Unh!

00:58.850 --> 01:00.226
- Where is it?
- I don't have it.

01:00.435 --> 01:03.598
Yeah?
My boss is not gonna like that.

01:06.817 --> 01:09.024
You got one day. You hear me?

01:17.578 --> 01:19.739
Listen, all you gotta do is pay up.

01:21.665 --> 01:24.532
You might wanna think about it.
You don't wanna do anything stupid.

01:39.516 --> 01:40.551
[GUNSHOT]

01:43.562 --> 01:45.348
[PANTING]

01:54.990 --> 01:56.526
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

01:57.701 --> 01:58.781
Yeah?

01:59.911 --> 02:03.074
- You all right?
- Yup, fine.

02:03.290 --> 02:06.908
You were talking in your sleep.
Yelling, actually.

02:09.755 --> 02:12.246
- Is that thing still out there?
- Yeah, looks like it.

02:12.466 --> 02:15.082
The hazmat suits haven't left.

02:15.302 --> 02:18.385
Julia, thanks again
for letting me crash here.

02:18.597 --> 02:22.089
With my husband missing
and everything that happened today,

02:22.309 --> 02:23.640
it was nice to have the company.

02:27.064 --> 02:30.227
- I'll see you in the morning.
- Great.

02:31.818 --> 02:33.024
Did you lose something?

02:33.236 --> 02:36.023
You didn't happen to see a pair
of dog tags around anywhere, did you?

02:36.239 --> 02:41.324
No, but I'll keep an eye out. Night.

02:54.216 --> 02:55.797
[SIREN WAILING]

03:00.764 --> 03:02.846
FREDDY:
Linda, Linda!

03:03.975 --> 03:05.590
- What the hell happened?
- Who shot Duke?

03:05.811 --> 03:08.143
No one shot Duke, Paul.
Calm down.

03:08.355 --> 03:10.971
He just got close to this thing
and his pacemaker exploded.

03:11.191 --> 03:12.476
[DOME HUMMING
AND FREDDY GRUNTS]

03:13.944 --> 03:14.979
Holy...

03:15.195 --> 03:16.776
If this thing blows up
mechanical things,

03:16.988 --> 03:19.274
then why didn't
Freddy's watch explode?

03:19.908 --> 03:22.991
It's a windup. It must only affect
things with batteries.

03:23.578 --> 03:26.866
Either way, just check the road blocks,
make sure nobody gets near this thing.

03:27.082 --> 03:29.289
PAUL: Who's in charge now?
- You're a cop. Do yourjob.

03:33.714 --> 03:36.797
- What about me?
- We need to take care of Duke.

03:41.471 --> 03:43.803
BEN: Joe, wait up.
- I'm fine.

03:44.015 --> 03:46.176
BEN: No, you're not. An hour ago
you were having a seizure,

03:46.393 --> 03:47.849
flopping around
like a fish on a hook.

03:48.061 --> 03:49.562
Did I say anything?

03:49.771 --> 03:52.387
Yeah, something about stars,
pink stars.

03:53.483 --> 03:56.520
- Anything you wanna tell me?
- No.

03:57.028 --> 04:02.193
- Hey, any luck, you guys?
MAN: Not yet. This thing goes down far.

04:02.659 --> 04:04.274
Oh, my God,
you know what all this means?

04:05.245 --> 04:07.031
We're so not having
that trig test tomorrow.

04:07.247 --> 04:10.455
- Trig. That's a great idea.
- It is?

04:10.667 --> 04:13.625
I could totally map this thing,
see if there's any holes.

04:13.837 --> 04:15.748
- I'm coming with you.
- Dude, you don't have to.

04:15.964 --> 04:19.707
Buddy, Lewis had Clark,
you got me, all right? Come on.

04:23.346 --> 04:27.464
Did you hear anything more about the
military on that contraption of yours?

04:27.684 --> 04:30.801
Nope, I lost the signal,
but I'm trying to get it back.

04:31.021 --> 04:33.603
It's not as easy as cueing up
the next Van Halen track.

04:33.815 --> 04:36.602
Now, why is it that engineers
always act superior to DJs?

04:36.818 --> 04:38.524
Because we're smarter, Phil.

04:39.070 --> 04:42.153
MAN [OVER RADIO]: Negative, sir.
Fire is ineffective against the sun‘ace,

04:42.365 --> 04:44.617
but we can conﬁrm
there is no radioactivity

04:44.826 --> 04:46.066
emanating from the dome.

04:46.286 --> 04:47.321
They did it again.

04:47.537 --> 04:49.323
Second time in 24 hours
they called it a dome.

04:49.539 --> 04:50.574
Yeah, I heard them.

04:50.791 --> 04:53.157
No, I don't think you did,
because you'd be freaking out too.

04:53.376 --> 04:54.661
We're under a dome, Dodee.

04:55.420 --> 04:57.035
Now, this is not
just some invisible wall

04:57.255 --> 04:59.337
where a chopper can drop in
and rescue us, man.

04:59.549 --> 05:01.335
- We gotta tell people.
- And we will.

05:01.551 --> 05:05.544
It's just right now we only know
enough to scare the crap out of them.

05:06.431 --> 05:07.807
To be continued.

05:10.644 --> 05:12.555
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
ON RADIO]

05:14.022 --> 05:15.353
[MUSIC STOPS]

05:15.941 --> 05:19.399
Faithful insomniacs, Phil Bushey here.
It's been a long night,

05:19.611 --> 05:22.148
and if you're listening to me,
it's because you've got no choice.

05:22.364 --> 05:28.906
You see, this barrier thing is blocking
all Of the cell phones, TV, Internet.

05:29.120 --> 05:30.951
Everything in our humble burg
of Chester's Mill.

05:31.164 --> 05:33.621
Theories about what's causing this
range from the North Koreans

05:33.834 --> 05:35.449
to a breach
in the space-time continuum...

05:35.669 --> 05:36.875
JIM:
Sorry I didn't get to you sooner.

05:37.087 --> 05:39.578
Had to make sure the clinic
and nursing home were taken care Of.

05:39.798 --> 05:41.584
You're kidding me.
If you're not careful,

05:41.800 --> 05:43.961
people are gonna start calling you
Santa Claus.

05:44.177 --> 05:45.212
[SWITCH CLICKS]

05:45.428 --> 05:48.044
Oh, God bless you, Jim Rennie.
How much do I owe you?

05:48.265 --> 05:49.880
JIM:
HO-hO-ho.

05:51.768 --> 05:57.388
Oh, my God. The lights are back.
Did that invisible wall come down?

05:57.607 --> 06:00.064
Well, I'm afraid not,
but we got gennies up and running.

06:00.277 --> 06:03.019
So we have some power. At least
get back to some sense Of normal.

06:03.238 --> 06:05.024
I don't believe we've met.

06:05.240 --> 06:08.983
Councilman Jim Rennie,
this iS Carolyn and her partner, Alice.

06:09.202 --> 06:11.739
They're staying in my spare room
upstairs. They're in from LA.

06:11.955 --> 06:13.991
We got trapped
driving through your little town.

06:14.207 --> 06:16.323
- We're taking our daughter Norrie tO--
- TO camp.

06:16.543 --> 06:18.625
But we have to get out Of here.
Our daughter is Sick.

06:18.837 --> 06:21.249
- She had a seizure.
- Does your girl have epilepsy?

06:21.464 --> 06:26.379
NO, it can happen to anyone.
Caffeine, sleep deprivation.

06:26.595 --> 06:31.180
- I've seen it in my patients.
- She's a psychiatrist.

06:31.391 --> 06:33.723
Well, I'm sorry you ladies aren't
discovering Chester's Mill

06:33.935 --> 06:36.017
under better circumstances,
but trust me,

06:36.229 --> 06:39.312
if you're gonna be stuck somewhere,
this iS the place to be.

06:39.524 --> 06:43.984
I've lived here my entire life
and no place I'd rather call home.

06:44.195 --> 06:46.857
Jim, I need you to come with me.

06:50.452 --> 06:51.487
Duke's dead.

06:58.001 --> 07:00.162
Look at me, damn it!

07:07.177 --> 07:08.963
Anyone?

07:13.850 --> 07:17.468
I wouldn't even bother. You could strip
naked in front Of these guys.

07:17.687 --> 07:19.473
They're still not gonna pay attention.

07:19.689 --> 07:21.850
I tried that an hour ago.
They didn't even blink.

07:23.944 --> 07:26.811
Oh, I looked around, by the way,
but no Sign of your dog tags.

07:27.030 --> 07:30.648
Oh, yeah, no worries. You know what?
I probablyjust left them in my car.

07:32.869 --> 07:35.906
So, what makes you think these guys
are under orders not to talk to us?

07:36.122 --> 07:37.453
Because they're not talking to us.

07:39.751 --> 07:42.493
Maybe they did this, you know.
Maybe they're responsible.

07:42.712 --> 07:45.419
- And why would they do that?
- I don't know.

07:45.632 --> 07:50.547
Could be an experiment.
Some sort Of portable detention camp.

07:50.762 --> 07:53.174
Maybe we're being used
as guinea pigs.

07:53.390 --> 07:54.971
Whatever it is,
these guys are the reason

07:55.183 --> 07:57.515
my husband is trapped out there.

08:06.277 --> 08:07.528
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

08:11.783 --> 08:14.866
- Where are you heading?
- The radio station.

08:15.078 --> 08:17.740
They might not be talking to us,
but they're talking to somebody.

08:28.591 --> 08:29.626
[DOOR RATTLING]

08:42.230 --> 08:44.437
I told you, you're safe with me.

08:45.191 --> 08:46.306
ANGIE:
Mr. Rennie!

08:46.526 --> 08:48.733
Mr. Rennie! Ah!

08:48.945 --> 08:50.276
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

08:50.488 --> 08:53.571
- Mr. Rennie! Mr. Rennie!
- Angie, my dad's not home.

08:53.783 --> 08:57.446
- Mr. Rennie, help!
- My dad's not home!

08:57.662 --> 09:01.746
Mr. Rennie! Let go Of me! Let go!

09:03.793 --> 09:06.375
NO! NO!

09:10.300 --> 09:11.881
NO!

09:13.011 --> 09:15.093
[ANGIE GRUNTING]

09:21.436 --> 09:24.769
- What the hell do you want from me?
- Look, I just want you to go back

09:24.981 --> 09:27.313
to being the Angie
I knew before yesterday.

09:29.444 --> 09:32.607
We were doing great
and then this thing comes down

09:32.822 --> 09:36.235
and you tell me to take a hike.

09:38.203 --> 09:40.034
I think it scrambled your brain.

09:41.122 --> 09:43.363
One of uS has a scrambled brain,
aHﬂght

09:44.125 --> 09:46.457
You can't see it, but I can.

09:48.088 --> 09:52.331
You're Sick, Angie,
but I'm gonna make you better.

09:55.095 --> 09:59.464
If I'm so sick, then why don't you
take me to the hospital?

09:59.682 --> 10:04.927
- If you care about me so much.
- Because he might still be there.

10:06.439 --> 10:11.024
- Who might still be there?
- The guy I saw you with.

10:12.278 --> 10:16.942
- What guy?
- Yesterday, outside the hospital.

10:17.617 --> 10:18.652
Barbie.

10:18.868 --> 10:20.984
The guy who came in
with Mrs. Shumway?

10:22.288 --> 10:24.700
- I don't even know him.
- Don't play dumb with me, Ange.

10:24.916 --> 10:28.249
- I can see right through you.
- All he did was give me a cigarette.

10:29.045 --> 10:30.080
Uh-huh.

10:32.549 --> 10:34.005
What did I ever do to you?

10:36.678 --> 10:39.385
- You loved me.
- No.

10:40.515 --> 10:45.009
- Junior, I never--
- Yes, Angie, you did.

10:45.228 --> 10:48.391
And when this thing comes down,
you're gonna love me again.

10:54.154 --> 10:56.110
I will never love you!

11:03.121 --> 11:04.156
You were right.

11:07.250 --> 11:13.211
That guy at the hospital,
we didn't just share a cigarette.

11:14.757 --> 11:18.796
He screwed my brains out
andllovedit

11:19.012 --> 11:21.879
I loved it more
than I ever did with you.

11:22.098 --> 11:25.261
You'll never be the man that he iS.

11:34.110 --> 11:38.274
Junior! Junior!

11:53.004 --> 11:57.168
Holy hell. He was a good man.

11:58.468 --> 11:59.548
I loved him.

12:01.763 --> 12:03.924
He was like a father to me.

12:06.601 --> 12:08.011
He was a good friend.

12:08.937 --> 12:12.976
Just before he died,
he tried to tell me something.

12:14.734 --> 12:16.099
Tried telling you what?

12:16.319 --> 12:19.732
He said there were things that
I didn't know about Chester's Mill.

12:19.948 --> 12:23.440
Things that he needed
to protect me from.

12:23.660 --> 12:25.400
What did that mean?

12:27.914 --> 12:29.495
I wish I could tell you.

12:33.878 --> 12:35.414
What am I gonna do
with another body?

12:36.381 --> 12:39.043
Cemetery's outside the barrier,
my freezer's full.

12:39.259 --> 12:41.966
JIM: Show some respect.
This isn't just another body.

12:42.679 --> 12:44.635
- This is Duke Perkins.
LESTER: What's that?

12:44.847 --> 12:48.214
Turn up your hearing aid, Lester.
I said, this iS Duke Perkins.

12:49.686 --> 12:54.225
Oh, no. Oh, good Lord.

12:56.609 --> 13:01.228
Deputy Esquivel,
I'm so sorry for your loss.

13:03.032 --> 13:06.991
Thank you, Reverend Coggins.
I Should get back out there.

13:07.203 --> 13:09.194
You're right, Linda.
GO out there and do yourjob.

13:09.414 --> 13:12.577
I'll make sure
Duke here gets taken care of.

13:20.717 --> 13:22.708
You're using our stuff.
You're high as a kite.

13:22.927 --> 13:27.296
So what? It's judgment day, Jim.
I might as well be feeling the rapture.

13:27.515 --> 13:30.257
The only reason we got into this
was to try to save Chester's Mill.

13:30.476 --> 13:33.058
NO, that's the reason Duke
went along with it.

13:33.271 --> 13:37.605
You and I, we had other priorities.
All right?

13:41.946 --> 13:46.906
I mean, at least now we don't have
to worry about him talking.

13:47.869 --> 13:49.279
Real man Of God there, rev.

13:51.539 --> 13:54.997
- Come on, let's go.
- What? Where are we going?

13:55.209 --> 13:57.370
TO clean up our meSS.

14:15.563 --> 14:17.599
Dude, found a way out. Check it.

14:17.857 --> 14:21.270
- Heh. You're such an idiot.
- Ha, ha, ha.

14:27.033 --> 14:29.695
BARBIE: It'S Joe, right?
- Yeah, McAlister.

14:29.911 --> 14:32.653
Dude, this iS the guy who saved
my ass when that plane went down.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.828
He totally said it was raining
arms and legs.

14:35.041 --> 14:37.407
Yeah, you could say that.
What are you up to?

14:37.627 --> 14:40.369
So far I marked these points. By
measuring the distance between them,

14:40.588 --> 14:42.294
I was able to come up with
the Y coordinate.

14:42.507 --> 14:44.247
And then by multiplying it
by its K integer--

14:44.467 --> 14:47.675
He connected the dots.
It's totally gonna be a circle.

14:47.887 --> 14:50.094
So far it looks like it's about
10 miles across.

14:50.681 --> 14:53.297
It covers the entire Mill,
including some Of Lake Eastpoint.

14:53.518 --> 14:57.227
- And you did this?
- Yeah, but we're being really careful.

14:57.438 --> 14:59.269
Keep it up.

15:01.401 --> 15:04.393
- Where did that guy come from?
- Definitely not from around here.

15:04.612 --> 15:06.352
How do you know?

15:07.865 --> 15:09.446
Because he's cool.

15:09.659 --> 15:12.867
- Come on, Dodee, you just had them.
- Patience, Phillip.

15:13.454 --> 15:14.990
[STATIC OVER RADIO]

15:15.748 --> 15:16.908
- Did you get something?
- Shh.

15:17.125 --> 15:20.333
MAN [OVER RADIO]: Air trafﬁc has
been rerouted around Chester’s Mill

15:20.545 --> 15:23.036
until further notice. We will continue
to monitor the air Space.

15:23.256 --> 15:24.621
JULIA:
What the hell iS that?

15:48.990 --> 15:52.403
Jim, what are you doing?

15:53.995 --> 15:57.158
I was, um, looking for that.

16:02.545 --> 16:04.410
It's Duke's will.

16:06.924 --> 16:08.789
GO ahead, read it.

16:20.730 --> 16:22.311
[SNIFFLING]

16:23.191 --> 16:28.686
He, uh, left me his house.
Everything.

16:28.905 --> 16:30.816
Of course he did.

16:31.699 --> 16:33.655
He treated you like the daughter
he never had.

16:35.411 --> 16:36.491
[SIGHS]

16:44.003 --> 16:45.743
[LINDA SOBBING]

16:46.506 --> 16:48.087
LINDA:
Now what do we do?

16:56.599 --> 16:58.965
That's a close call, no thanks to you.

16:59.185 --> 17:02.052
What was I supposed to do,
phone you?

17:02.271 --> 17:05.013
- SO, what did you find out?
- Nothing to do with propane.

17:05.233 --> 17:06.973
Duke must have kept the records
at his house.

17:07.193 --> 17:09.400
Yeah, it's not his house anymore.
He left it to the girl.

17:09.612 --> 17:11.273
So you better get over there
before she does.

17:11.489 --> 17:15.698
- Me? What are you gonna do?
- My job, Lester. Now get out.

17:15.910 --> 17:17.866
I'm the only councilman left
in Chester's Mill.

17:18.079 --> 17:20.320
Got a town to take care Of.

17:26.128 --> 17:28.961
JULIA: You made this?
- Yeah, I'm only three credits short

17:29.173 --> 17:31.164
of my master's degree
in electrical engineering.

17:31.384 --> 17:32.419
JULIA:
Wow.

17:32.635 --> 17:33.670
- Yeah.
- How does it work?

17:35.221 --> 17:38.384
Well, this iS a harmonic microwave
frequency converter.

17:38.599 --> 17:41.762
It turns low frequency waves into high
frequency waves so that we can hear--

17:41.978 --> 17:47.189
- Maybe you should just let me hear it.
- Okay, sometimes it's hard to pick up.

17:47.400 --> 17:49.106
[STATIC ON RADIO]

17:49.360 --> 17:52.648
MAN [ON RADIO]: Further tests reveal
the dome appears to be impervious

17:52.863 --> 17:55.696
to high-energy lasers
and all class-8 corrosive chemicals.

17:55.908 --> 17:58.991
- We're under a dome.
- Yeah, that's what they keep calling it.

17:59.203 --> 18:03.162
- Why haven't you told anybody?
- We're not a news station.

18:05.668 --> 18:07.374
Hey,Phw

18:08.170 --> 18:10.502
That was some face-melting
rock 'n' roll brought to you by--

18:10.715 --> 18:12.046
- I'm going on.
DODEE: I tried to stop her.

18:12.258 --> 18:14.465
- I'm sorry, what are you doing?
JULIA: Going on the air.

18:14.677 --> 18:15.837
NO, you can't.

18:16.053 --> 18:19.386
This iS Julia Shumway from
The Weekly Independent.

18:19.599 --> 18:23.512
I have some news for all Of us
stuck here inside Chester's Mill.

18:24.270 --> 18:27.603
l have just learned that the barrier
around Chester's Mill

18:27.815 --> 18:29.430
is being called a dome.

18:30.109 --> 18:32.600
This information appears
to be coming from military sources

18:32.820 --> 18:37.314
positioned just outside Chester's Mill,
just outside the dome.

18:37.533 --> 18:40.696
We will keep updating you
as information comes in.

18:40.911 --> 18:42.617
So stay tuned to...

18:42.830 --> 18:48.951
WYBS, your only source of news
from under the dome.

18:52.381 --> 18:56.374
- What does that mean?
- I have no idea.

18:57.303 --> 18:59.214
I do, Mom.

19:01.015 --> 19:03.677
It means we're all gonna die in here.

19:08.105 --> 19:10.221
ROSE:
This dome thing, how big is it?

19:10.441 --> 19:11.977
- No idea.
- We're under a dome?

19:12.193 --> 19:13.649
MAN:
We gonna run out Of air?

19:13.861 --> 19:15.817
Until I find out where Julia
got this information,

19:16.030 --> 19:17.895
I think it's best
that we just all stay calm.

19:18.115 --> 19:21.278
- What if it collapses on us?
- Great, now the Sky iS falling.

19:21.494 --> 19:26.033
If we keep our heads and we stick
together, we'll get through this.

19:29.168 --> 19:33.207
Hey, "We'll get through this"? You don't
know what this dome thing might do.

19:33.422 --> 19:36.038
Right, but the last thing we need
right now is for people to panic.

19:36.258 --> 19:38.169
That thing took Duke. Who's next?

19:38.386 --> 19:40.547
Pull yourself together
and get out on patrol.

19:40.763 --> 19:43.505
